{"schema_version":"1","crate":"langkit_support","version":"26.0.0","id":"95fd2b442d6c69a1","name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers","qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers","kind":"ada_package","location":{"file":"../../../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/gnatcoll_gmp_26.0.0_dacec6f3/242aa4cd4e9577b95d7699186629be7359b559da44c5f7e45241e32597386b75/gmp/gnatcoll-gmp-integers.ads","line":49,"column":9},"code":"package GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers","documentation":{"description":"This package defines an arbitrary precision integer type based on the\nunderlying GNU Multiple Precision library. The name of the type is\n\"Big_Integer.\"\n\nMost Ada operations and operators are supported for type Big_Integer,\nexcept that the type is limited private in order to enforce the underlying\nsemantics required by the library implementation. Assignment is performed\nvia the Set routines, and the equality operator is explicitly defined.\n\nMost of the Ada routines are direct calls to the underlying C routines,\nexcept where the Ada semantics differ. The routines all have pragma Inline\napplied so that no additional overhead is incurred over that of a direct\ncall to the C routine (when the body consists of only such a call).\n\nNote that using the operators returning Big_Integer objects will result in\ntemporaries, except when used as the initial value in object declarations.\nThese temporaries are automatically initialized when created but will thus\nincur some overhead. Procedural versions of the arithmetic operators are\ntherefore included, matching those of the underlying GMP library in C\n(except in name), which avoid temporaries and operate directly on the\noperands."},"tagged_types":[{"id":"573f0b373543546b","name":"Big_Integer","qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.Big_Integer","kind":"ada_tagged_type","location":{"file":"../../../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/gnatcoll_gmp_26.0.0_dacec6f3/242aa4cd4e9577b95d7699186629be7359b559da44c5f7e45241e32597386b75/gmp/gnatcoll-gmp-integers.ads","line":53,"column":9},"code":"type Big_Integer is tagged limited private;","documentation":{"description":"The type is limited because clients should not use predefined\nassignment; nor should they use predefined equality. This matches the\nsemantics of the underlying GMP library in C. For assignment, use the\nSet routines. The equality operator is explicitly redefined."},"dispatching_declared":[{"qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.\"*\"","id":"da57cc4447a5af53","unit":"gnatcoll-gmp-integers"},{"qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.\"*\"","id":"eda42ebe489fba33","unit":"gnatcoll-gmp-integers"},{"qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.\"*\"","id":"dc3fa8140ff54592","unit":"gnatcoll-gmp-integers"},{"qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.\"**\"","id":"2ab95ee52088dcdb","unit":"gnatcoll-gmp-integers"},{"qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.\"+\"","id":"5d37072c4eb5de27","unit":"gnatcoll-gmp-integers"},{"qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.\"+\"","id":"396f5955818a733e","unit":"gnatcoll-gmp-integers"},{"qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.\"+\"","id":"a7e292d027938951","unit":"gnatcoll-gmp-integers"},{"qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.\"-\"","id":"118b6e0370dba58c","unit":"gnatcoll-gmp-integers"},{"qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.\"-\"","id":"cf66b837a054b169","unit":"gnatcoll-gmp-integers"},{"qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.\"-\"","id":"60924ad584b65728","unit":"gnatcoll-gmp-integers"},{"qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.\"-\"","id":"30c861c15c19457c","unit":"gnatcoll-gmp-integers"},{"qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.\"/\"","id":"88da028b6bdec9fb","unit":"gnatcoll-gmp-integers"},{"qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.\"/\"","id":"86a85e45e0498c3a","unit":"gnatcoll-gmp-integers"},{"qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.\"<\"","id":"287834ae6cafa26d","unit":"gnatcoll-gmp-integers"},{"qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.GMP.Integers.\"<\"","id":"5468f7382492b333","unit":"gnatcoll-gmp-integers"},{"qualified_name":"GNA